I am trying to go again next Saturday. The weather doesn't look so good right now, but it's still Monday.
It is already clear where the problems lie. It will probably be VERY difficult to get the medical approval, due to the FAA's opinion on certain medications.
It is not impossible, but it will take VERY long and involves a LOT of extra work.
This is somewhat discouraging, but it's just another problem that has to be solved. So far, it seems solvable. It just takes a lot of time and money.
If you want to know what lies ahead for me.
The FAA is not a fan of ADHD. They definitely won't give you medical clearance if you're taking medication for it.
